    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Insertion Sort</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: monospace;\n            font-size: 14px;\n            text-align: left;\n            padding: 10px;\n            background-color: #f0f0f0;\n        }\n        label {\n            display: block;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        input[type=\"number\"] {\n            width: 50px;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n        select {\n            width: 50px;\n            margin-bottom: 10px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Insertion Sort</h1>\n<h2>How it works:</h2>\n<p>Insertion Sort is a simple sorting algorithm that works by iterating through a list of elements one by one. It compares each element with its adjacent elements and inserts it into its correct position in the sorted list.</p>\n\n<h2>How to use:</h2>\n<ul>\n    <li>Enter a list of numbers separated by commas.</li>\n    <li>Press the \"Sort\" button to run the algorithm.</li>\n    <li>Press the \"Reset\" button to clear the list.</li>\n    <li>Press the \"Help\" button to view the algorithm's steps.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"input\" placeholder=\"Enter a list of numbers separated by commas\">\n<button id=\"sort\">Sort</button>\n<select id=\"step\">\n    <option value=\"1\">Step 1: No swaps</option>\n    <option value=\"2\">Step 2: Swap elements if they are in wrong order</option>\n    <option value=\"3\">Step 3: Repeat steps 1 and 2 until no swaps are needed</option>\n    <option value=\"4\">Step 4: Output sorted list</option>\n</select>\n<button id=\"reset\">Reset</button>\n<button id=\"help\">Help</button>\n\n<div id=\"output\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    const input = document.getElementById('input');\n    const sort = document.getElementById('sort');\n    const step = document.getElementById('step');\n    const reset = document.getElementById('reset');\n    const help = document.getElementById('help');\n    const output = document.getElementById('output');\n\n    const numbers = input.value.split(',').map(Number);\n    let sorted = numbers.slice();\n    let steps = 0;\n\n    function swap(arr, i, j) {\n        [arr[i], arr[j]] = [arr[j], arr[i]];\n    }\n\n    function insertionSort(arr) {\n        for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {\n            let key = arr[i];\n            let j = i - 1;\n\n            while (j >= 0 && arr[j] > key) {\n                swap(arr, j, j - 1);\n                steps++;\n            }\n\n            if (i == j + 1) {\n                swap(arr, i, j + 1);\n                steps++;\n            }\n        }\n\n        return arr;\n    }\n\n    function sortFunction() {\n        sorted = insertionSort(numbers);\n        output.innerHTML = '';\n        steps = 0;\n\n        for (let i = 0; i < sorted.length; i++) {\n            output.innerHTML += `${i + 1}: ${sorted[i]}\\n`;\n        }\n    }\n\n    sort.addEventListener('click', sortFunction);\n\n    reset.addEventListener('click', () => {\n        sorted = numbers.slice();\n        steps = 0;\n\n        output.innerHTML = '';\n        for (let i = 0; i < sorted.length; i++) {\n            output.innerHTML += `${i + 1}: ${sorted[i]}\\n`;\n        }\n    });\n\n    help.addEventListener('click', () => {\n        alert('Insertion Sort steps:');\n        alert('Step 1: No swaps');\n        alert('Step 2: Swap elements if they are in wrong order');\n        alert('Step 3: Repeat steps 1 and 2 until no swaps are needed');\n        alert('Step 4: Output sorted list');\n    });\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
